&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse- Cataract Treatment Centre&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join our centre of Excellence in Ophthalmology. The post holder will work as part of a large team who are providing high quality day case cataract surgery. The successful candidate will have an interest in the speciality and theatre environment and will be given the opportunity and training to work across every stage of the patient’s pathway including Outpatients, Pre-assessment and Day Case Theatre. The service provides care at outreach clinics as well as base hospital. There is an excellent Preceptorship programme in place to support the post-holders professional development. Previous Ophthalmic or theatre skills desirable but not essential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A new registrant, or a registrant moving into the NHS for the first time,will be supported through our six month multi-professional Preceptorship programme, by our Preceptorship Lead and in clinical practice by an allocated and experienced clinical practitioner (a preceptor). We will provide guidance, support and feedback throughout your transitional period, while your develop the necessary knowledge and skills in becoming a confident and competent practitioner.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At STSFT we recognise the importance of ensuring healthy, happy staff and we are committed to providing a number of benefits to our staff – &lt;em&gt;to review these, please see attached link&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this vacancy is not suitable for overseas trained nurses wishing to join the Trust as an Adaptation Nurse. These vacancies will be advertised via NHS Jobs when they arise.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
